President Trump's second trip abroad aims to promote economic prosperity worldwide and emphasize the United States' commitment to global leadership. He will visit Poland and attend the G20 Summit in Germany. The goals of the trip include reaffirming America's commitment to its allies, building a constructive relationship with Russia, and addressing the nuclear threat from North Korea. President Trump also seeks fair and balanced international relationships, insisting that all allies pay their fair share. He plans to counteract unfair economic practices and create an open and fair energy market. The President hopes to convey that his America First agenda considers the needs of the United States' partners abroad and believes that long-term peace and international prosperity require US leadership and engagement with the world.